From: Kamil Lulko <limakzagan@gmail.com>
Subject: dxvk: skip VK_EXT_transform_feedback on Adreno (vkCreateDevice reject)

Adreno (Qualcomm proprietary, driver 0.762.41) returns
VK_ERROR_FEATURE_NOT_PRESENT from vkCreateDevice when the
VK_EXT_transform_feedback features struct is in the device pNext chain,
even with the feature value gated. A pNext-chain bisect (patch 0002,
surfaced via triage-vst-log.py while debugging AmpliTube 5's black
editor) proved removing only this struct makes vkCreateDevice succeed.
Disable the extension for Qualcomm so initFeatureChain skips the struct.
Transform feedback only adds an optional stream-output buffer bit
(gated on the feature) so the allocator is unaffected — unlike
robustness2 which was load-bearing.

diff --git a/src/dxvk/dxvk_adapter.cpp b/src/dxvk/dxvk_adapter.cpp
index 1285c4ee..923caddd 100644
--- a/src/dxvk/dxvk_adapter.cpp
+++ b/src/dxvk/dxvk_adapter.cpp
@@ -298,6 +298,26 @@ namespace dxvk {
     if (!m_deviceExtensions.supports(devExtensions.extPageableDeviceLocalMemory.name()))
       devExtensions.amdMemoryOverallocationBehaviour.setMode(DxvkExtMode::Optional);
 
+    /* Adreno (Qualcomm proprietary) returns VK_ERROR_FEATURE_NOT_PRESENT
+     * from vkCreateDevice when the VK_EXT_transform_feedback features
+     * struct is present in the device pNext chain — even with the feature
+     * value gated to reported support. A pNext-chain bisect (added by
+     * patch 0002, surfaced via triage-vst-log.py while debugging
+     * AmpliTube 5's black editor on Adreno 750 / driver 0.762.41) proved
+     * removing JUST this struct makes vkCreateDevice succeed.
+     *
+     * Disabling the extension makes initFeatureChain's
+     * `if (devExtensions.extTransformFeedback)` guard skip the struct and
+     * leaves features().extTransformFeedback.transformFeedback false.
+     * Unlike VK_EXT_robustness2 (load-bearing for the global-buffer
+     * suballocator's robustBufferAccess2 alignment — gating it broke
+     * DxvkMemoryAllocator), transform feedback only contributes an
+     * OPTIONAL stream-output buffer-usage bit in dxvk_memory.cpp gated on
+     * that feature, so the bit is simply not added. D3D11 stream-output
+     * (SO stage) becomes unavailable, which 2D plugin UIs never use. */
+    if (m_deviceInfo.vk12.driverID == VK_DRIVER_ID_QUALCOMM_PROPRIETARY)
+      devExtensions.extTransformFeedback.setMode(DxvkExtMode::Disabled);
+
     DxvkNameSet extensionsEnabled;
 
     if (!m_deviceExtensions.enableExtensions(
